com.ibm.team.build.common.model

Interface IBuildDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IBuildDefinitionHandle, IBuildItem, IBuildItemHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle

    public interface IBuildDefinition
extends IBuildDefinitionHandle, IAuditable, IBuildItem
    The build definition is a primary identifier for a set of builds. A definition is composed of one or more configuration elements that make up the configurable data in the definition. Example configuration elements provided by com.ibm.team.build are General, Ant, Schedule, Expected Contributions, and Properties. In addition, new configuration elements can be contributed via the com.ibm.team.build.common.buildConfigurationElements extension point.
    Since:
    0.5

      • copyDefinition

        IBuildDefinition copyDefinition()
        Make a copy of this definition.
        Returns:
        The new build definition. It is a working copy and has not been saved. The origin is not set. The new copy has a different UUID than the original. The new copy has a clear history. The remainder of the contents are equal to the original.

      • initializeConfiguration

        void initializeConfiguration(IBuildConfigurationElement element)
        Initialize the build definition from the given configuration element. The element is added to the definition after existing configuration elements. In addition, the generic properties declared in the element's extension are copied into the build definition.

        If an element with the same id is already present in the definition, it is overwritten at its current position.

        This method may be called more than once with different configuration elements.

        Parameters:
        element - The configuration element to initialize the definition with.

      • initializeConfiguration

        void initializeConfiguration(IBuildDefinitionTemplate template)
        Initialize the build definition from the given template. The configuration elements specified by the template are copied into the definition. In addition, the generic properties declared in the template's extension are copied into the build definition. Any existing elements in the definition are overwritten by template elements with the same id. Likewise, any existing generic properties will be overwritten by template properties with the same name.

        This method may be called more than once with different templates.

        Parameters:
        template - The template to initialize the definition with.
